---
import Layout from '@layouts/BlogPost.astro'
---

<Layout
	title="My Code/Artwork Usage Terms"
	description="Terms and conditions for using my code and artwork."
	pubDate={new Date('July 04 2026')}
>
	<h3>Hello!</h3>
	<p>
		I write my own code and design the artwork on this site, except where otherwise noted. I am no expert by any means when it comes to either, but I have been slowly getting better. I love the indie web, and a big part of this community is helping other people design their own websites. Thus, I am happy to help newbies coding their own websites. Don't be afraid to <a href="mailto:aristocraticarietta@proton.me">reach out via E-Mail and ask questions!</a> I promise I don't bite, and I really do want to help.
	</p>
	<h3>See something you like? Here's how to look "under the hood":</h3>
	<p>
		If you see something interesting on this site, go ahead and press <kbd>F12</kbd> or <kbd>Ctrl (Cmd on Mac) + Shift + I</kbd> to open the developer tools panel. You can also <kbd>right click</kbd> on an interesting element and click <kbd>Inspect</kbd> in the menu that pops up to open the panel to that element exactly.
	</p>
	<h3>Want to use my code/artwork on your own site?</h3>
	<p>
		<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/">All of my work is licencsed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.</a> Basically, this boils down to: You can use, adapt, remix, or transform up my work(s) in any medium or format <i>however</i> you must give appropriate credit back to me (see section below on proper attribution), you may <b>not</b> use the work(s) for commercial purposes, and if you share an adapted, remixed, or transformed version of my work you must share it under the same license.
	</p>
	<h3>Attribution</h3>
	<p>
		While I do require attribution for my work, the best way to credit me is subjective and I trust you to choose an option that feels appropriate to you. If you are using my work on an indie web site, I recommend adding my button to your site somewhere. I've even made it easy for you to add my button to your web site as <a href="/fun-stuff/#button-link"> I have already written code for you to copy and paste </a> that includes a link back to me. If you use a blinky I make, an easy way to attribute me is to wrap the blinky in an <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tag, just like the button code above. Also, if you want to just provide my link in somewhere like a credits/links page, that is perfectly fine too! Just make sure you link to <a href="/">aristocratic-arietta.neocities.org</a> and I'm happy.
	</p>
</Layout>